main event: Two observers saw an oval-shaped, red-orange glowing object hovering above the area near Honda Ridge Road.
interesting points: The object appeared to have a lighter center and be lit up.
The observers could not locate the object when they rounded the hill to where it should have been visible again.
The observers were familiar with conventional aircraft but could not identify the object with anything they had seen before.
The weather conditions included a 1000 ft ceiling, haze, and rain at the time of the sighting.
The preparing officer believed the object observed was likely a round vehicle traveling up Honda Canyon Road, due to the weather and foliage in the area.
location: Honda Ridge Road, Vandenberg AFB, California
witnesses: two observers, one a 1Lt USAF motion picture photographer
